<h4 id="input-parameters">Input Parameters</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Unlike C++, Java, which have an entry point, we can pass actual parameters
to formal parameters.</li>
  <li>In Shell script, it design a new way to accept input parameters</li>
</ol>

<div class="language-shell highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c"># $0: name of executable file</span>
<span class="c"># $1, $2: first and second parameters of the program</span>
<span class="c"># $@: all input parameters</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<div class="language-shell highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">for </span>i <span class="k">in</span> <span class="k">*</span>.md
<span class="k">do
   </span><span class="nv">var1</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">i</span>:0:10<span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">"</span>
   <span class="nv">var2</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">i</span>:10:100<span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">"</span>
   <span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">var1</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">-code</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">var2</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">"</span>
   <span class="nb">mv</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">i</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">"</span> <span class="s2">"</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">var1</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">-code</span><span class="k">${</span><span class="nv">var2</span><span class="k">}</span><span class="s2">"</span>
<span class="k">done</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

